#
# Architectural pattern: Rust prefers
# event-stream parsers for zero-allocation
# efficiency; Go + Node prefer AST-based
# parsers for easier extension composition.
# This is consistent with each language's
# idioms (Rust's emphasis on zero-cost
# abstractions; Go + Node's emphasis on
# pragmatic composability).
#
